Posts.Content: In case this did not reach you before here goes. I am 73, and had a DRE and PSA about 10 years before diagnosis. DRE was smooth but PSA was 3.9. I decided that I was not going to allow anyone do that to me again. Bad mistake. I did not have any symptoms to speak of. Got up at night once in a while,no pain, no blood in urine or semen. I did break a couple of ribs when I fell in 2013, but what drove me to the doctor was the loss of 10 pounds a week after I reached my 177 pound goal. This was not good. PCP PSA 2was 1696 and 2 weeks later at urologist it was 1860 ng/ml. I then had DRE and TRUS/PNB-like driving a Kubota up my butt-a lot of pain--Not fun. I was raised in Connecticut, lived n Virginia, North Carolina and New Orleans before settling in Maine. I purchase milled flaxseed which I grind fresh in my coffee grinder every morning. That way it is always fresh and there are no digestive issues. No surgery possible, just ADT (Firm-a-gon) and there is a message there along with XGeva for osteoporosis. ED, and I had to fight for my TriMix injectable. Overall I am well except for my orthopedic issues which, I have been told are not cancer related. I did not intend for this to be as long as it is, but I tried to give you all the information you requested, and how I am really doing.

Posts.Content: This is my first post to this site. I was diagnosed with Prostate Cancer November 10th 2014. I have highly active Adenocarcinoma of the prostate with lymphadenopathy and bone mets. Gleason (4+5) 9, stage IV. Treatment was Firmagon Nov 10th 2014 followed by Taxotere December 1st 2014 for 6 cycles 3 weeks apart. PSA has gone as follows: Date P.S.A. ng/ml Friday, October 17, 2014 1696.00 Wednesday, October 22, 2014 1860.00 Friday, November 21, 2014 696.00 Wednesday, December 10, 2014 72.60 Monday, January 5, 2015 22.60 Monday, February 2, 2015 9.40 Monday, March 2, 2015 4.60 Monday, March 30, 2015 1.79 Wednesday, April 29, 2015 0.49 Wednesday, May 27, 2015 0.31 Wednesday, June 24, 2015 0.19 Wednesday, July 22, 2015 0.18 Monday, August 17, 2015 0.29 Tuesday, August 18, 2015 0.35 Wednesday, September 16, 2015 0.15 Monday, October 19, 2015 0.15 Wednesday, November 18, 2015 0.31 Wednesday, December 23, 2015 0.27 Monday, January 25, 2016 0.32 Monday. February 29, 2016 0.40 Tuesday March 15, 2016 0.56 Wednesday, March 30, 2016 0.38 Wednesday, April 27th 2016 0.50 Any time there is a bump up there has been too much sitting time and not enough exercise. I have added 2 Tbsp. of flaxseed /day to the regimen. 2 x 500 mg Metformin, 40 mg Atorvastatin. I am about to add Artemisinin and iron as an additional adjunct based on some research I have read. Any thoughts from anyone. I am not a doctor, but I am a scientist with an MA in Biology and a lot of chemistry.
Posts.Title: Firstpost

Posts.Content: Went for monthly check-up today. PSA 0.58, everything else stable. N.P. suggested go to the pool since I have some orthopedic issues. Told not to worry about bump up from 0.5 to 0.58 ng/ml. Too much time sitting, and not enough exercise. That has to change. The Metformin and higher atorvastatin was my idea based on research. Likewise the Flaxseed and upcoming artemisinin (sweet wormwood) again based on my research combined with iron and vitamin C. Still on Firm-a-gon and XGeva. So ADT still in place.

Posts.Content: As noted before I have found a new group to deal with me. I am now much happier. After I was started on Casodex on June 29th and my urologist could not or would not tell me about side effects other than to look it up on the internet. When I came up with diarrhea as a result I was told to go to my PCP. I found a new group much more in touch with treatments and possibilities for me. We discussed several options including Provenge and Xofigo. The decision has been made to try the Provenge first. I have now had two treatments with the third coming on November 18th. My PSA had gone up to 1.45. but last month it had come down to 1.28. I understand that PSA may not come down initially, but I can live in hope. We will see about a CT scan at the end of December. If anyone has had experience with Provenge immunotherapy, I would like to hear their results. I was diagnosed with Prostate Cancer November 10th 2014. I have highly active Adenocarcinoma of the prostate with lymphadenopathy and bone mets. Gleason (4+5) 9, stage IV. Treatment was Firmagon Nov 10th 2014 followed by Taxotere December 1st 2014 for 6 cycles 3 weeks apart. Posts.Content: I noted after my second cycle with Taxotere that I had a loss of sensitivity in my fingers, down the front of my legs and out onto my feet. I was asked about it and did not admit to it because I did not want to stop the Chemo, putting my life at risk. Since the Chemo was finished and more recently the loss of sensitivity has gotten worse as has my loss of balance. Has anyone else had this reaction or side effect? Has it improved over time? What kind of treatment has been initiated? I was diagnosed with Prostate Cancer November 10th 2014. I have highly active Adenocarcinoma of the prostate with lymphadenopathy and bone mets. Posts.Content: Everything seems to be moving in the right direction. My only question in the last 2 reports is the prognosis which states that it is "guarded". The bone scan in September was "improved". If the bone mets are being attacked by the treatment how can the prognosis be "guarded". What are the thoughts on the length of the runway? I have now survived 2 years on ADT plus chemotherapy. My replaced knee seems to be working better and better. My vision after cataract surgery is now 20/20. It was never that good. I am looking forward to the third Provenge infusion a week from tomorrow. After that I hope my cells will do the job and reduce my bone mets, main tumor and the circulating tumor cells. Only time will tell.
